pageContext.claim: “But the rallies, again, are outdoor and we have heard of no incidences where [covid-19 was spread] -- and I've had big rallies, we're having 35,000, 40,000 people come at the rallies, and we had no incidence where we had -- we have had a problem.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump's rallies are not as large as he would like to think. Regardless, Kaiser Health News reported a Stanford University study found the president’s campaign rallies have led to more than 700 Covid-19 related deaths.
